values:
Just got home from Matt Zambo's house, watched a movie there, had good company.... Before that i was at the PR park watching the fireworks, it was actually really awesome, i was expecting it to be really lame.  So reciently life has consisted of chillin' with good friends and having good times, without any kind of drama or anything.  Outside of the house that is.... my mom has been a nazi reciently, all of the suddon she doesn't trust me with anything, and its really frustrating.

Well, my last entry before i go to the youth leadership thingamagig... So heres the deal... I get dropped at the train station with 3 big ass bags, then i take it to grand central, subway to penn station, penn station to D.C. and taxi to the camp... its going to be a bitch.  I leave for 10 days and after that i stay for another day and visit some colleges then i come home for about a week.  And after that week i'm gone till the 12th of August.

I'm mad tired, and i dont have anything of much substance to say... so if you love me leave me a comment or email me dkurzewick@yahoo.com or call me (914-552-7832) or visit me, or just give your body to me.  Anywho... Peace out bitches!

-dave

What up bitches.... I'm in a funky mood today.  Overall, things have been pretty hectic, trying to think deep thoughts when everything and everyone around me isn't serious at all.  But, other than that, i have two new sisters (Kristina and Liz) and they are the bestest.

Well, the summer offically started when we all camped out at the morrissey residence (me, alanna, liz, alex, randall, kristen, mel (at the end)) and made smores and other goodies.  Although nobody really slept, it was awesome... and gazing at the stars made me realize that i love astronomy... i haven't EVER thought of any field i could possibly love in my life so this is a revelation.....  Like, i mean, i really wanna be an astronomer.  Well, back to the story:  After the camping we went to the beach which was awesome.

After somemore drama i've just been having a good time, i'm so very lucky that i have the friends i have, honestly.

Just getting prepared for the rest of my summer, road test the 2nd, i leave the 5th i think then i'm gone playing soccer till august...  I'm really excited, only a bit scared my shoulder will die, but whatevs!

Well, i'm about to go to verizon to get my new phone, peace out gangstaz..
-kurz
